sed to describe the American frontier. In Klein's words, "We remain obscurely entangled in philosophies of history we no longer profess, and the very idea of 'America' balances on history's shifting frontiers."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFrontier and pioneer lifexHistoriographyxUnited States. 0aFrontier and pioneer lifezUnited StatesxHistoriography. 0aFrontier thesis. 0aHistoriographyxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aHistoriographyxHistoryy20th centuryxUnited States. 0aHistoriographyzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndians of North AmericaxFirst contact with EuropeansxHistoriography. 0aIndians of North AmericaxFirst contact with other peoplesxHistoriography. 0aIndians, Treatment ofxHistoriographyxNorth America. 0aIndians, Treatment ofzNorth AmericaxHistoriography. 4acivilization. 4ademocracy. 4ahistory of the Americas. 4ahistory. 4aimagination. 4aknowledge. 4amemory. 4anation. 4aphilosophy. 4apublic. 4asociology. 4aspace. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520924185?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520924185423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520924185/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles